    caption: [The constructed E. coli plasmid pBR322. Note the location of some important restriction sites—for PstI, EcoRI, BamHI, SalI, and PvuII; ampicillin- and tetracycline-resistance genes; and the replication origin (ori). Constructed in 1977, this was one of the early plasmids designed expressly for cloning in E. coli. 4. The small size of the plasmid (4,361 bp) facilitates],
