  "9-14": (
    caption: [Building a cDNA library from mRNA. A cell’s total mRNA content includes transcripts from thousands of genes, and the cDNAs generated from this mRNA are correspondingly heterogeneous. Reverse transcriptase can synthesize DNA on an RNA or a DNA template (see Fig. 26–32). To prime the synthesis of a second DNA strand, oligonucle- otides of known sequence are ligated to the 3(cid:4) end of the first strand, and the double-stranded cDNA so produced is cloned into a plasmid. c09DNABasedInformationTechnologies.indd Page 333 18/09/12 2:07 PM user-F408 c09DNABasedInformationTechnologies.indd Page 333 18/09/12 2:07 PM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop],
