  "9-16": (
    caption: [Green fluorescent protein (GFP). (a) The GFP protein (PDB ID 1GFL), derived from the jellyfish Aequorea victoria, has a (cid:2)- barrel structure; the fluorophore (shown as a space-filling model) is in the center of the barrel. (b) Variants of GFP are now available in al- most any color of the visible spectrum. (c) A GLR1-GFP fusion protein fluoresces bright green in Caenorhabditis elegans, a nematode worm (left). GLR1 is a glutamate receptor of nervous tissue. (Autofluoresc- ing fat droplets are false colored in magenta.) The membranes of E. coli cells (right) are stained with a red fluorescent dye. The cells are expressing a protein that binds to a resident plasmid, fused to GFP. The green spots indicate the locations of plasmids.],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
