    caption: [Enlarged image of a DNA microarray. Each glowing spot contains DNA from one of the roughly 6,500 genes of the yeast (S. cerevi- siae) genome, with every gene represented in the array. The microarray has been probed with fluorescently labeled nucleic acid derived from mRNAs obtained when the cells were growing in culture (green) and 5 hours after they began to form spores (red). The green spots represent genes expressed at higher levels during growth; the red spots, genes expressed at higher levels during sporulation. The yellow spots represent genes that do not change their level of expression during sporulation. This image is enlarged; the microarray actually measures only 1.8 (cid:2) 1.8 cm.],
